Exaggerate: The claim exaggerates the notion that China allowed flights out of Wuhan while blocking flights into other cities in China.
Lack enough support: The claim lacks sufficient evidence or support to prove that China allowed flights out of Wuhan to Western cities while blocking flights within China.
Problematic assumption: The claim assumes that China may have sought to protect itself by allowing infections to spread to other countries, without providing substantial evidence to support this assumption.
Exist alternative explanation: The claim fails to consider alternative explanations for the flight restrictions, such as public health measures or containment efforts by the Chinese government.
